## What is constructor 
A constrcutor is a special method that runs when you  create a new object with keyword "new"
**It has the same name as class but no return type, it called automatically when an object is created

## this refers to the current object instance. It's commonly used in constructors to distinguished between field and a parameter 
e.g- this.name 

## Methods & Parametrs 
methods are blocks of  reusable code that perform specific tasks.They can accept input parameters and return output values.
It defines behaviour of an object 


##Java has garbage collector  hence java has no deconstructor.


